            <thetext>cyrus 2.4.12-2 on ubuntu precise
virtual environment with KVM

A setting for the mupdate master with prefork more than 1 in cyrus.conf leads
to misbehaviour of the mupdate process.
Updates in the mailbox list are not sent reliable to the frontends any more.
This results in incorrect entries in mailbox.db on the frontends.

The mupdate sessions between frontend and master are still open and functional.
There aren&apos;t any problems in the communication between backend and master.</thetext>
